24—06-2022: Day-3 Git Beginning Tutorial
Git install/setup
Create folder and right click and select git bash
git init
git status //To check git is initiated
git config –global user.name “Bhargava Chiliveru”
git config –global user.email cbkrishna510@gmail.com
git config –list  //To check the user name/email is registered
//To remove user name/email
git config –global –unset user.name
git config –global –unset user.email 
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
25-06-2022 
Touch file1 //linux  command to create file
ls //to see the file is created
git status //to see where the file is  workspace or staging/index or local repo…it should be in workspace and in red colour
git add file1 //to move file from work space to staging
git status // file should be in green colour
git commit -m “Sample Commit” file1
git log //to see files in local repo commitid or shacode
--------------cid//commit id 
git show cid 
//add multiple files
git add file3 file4 file5
or
git add .
or
git add *
or git add -A
git reset head //to revert file from staging to workspace
git reset –soft cid //to revert file from local repo to staging** (n-1) user previous cid to reset the current one
git reset –mixed cid //to revert file from local repo to workspace also file in staging will be moved to workspace
Modified file can be moved from workspace to local repo
git diff //to see what changes are done on file..this can be used to see before we commit the code
git show cid //to see modified/created code/data which is committed
26-june-2022
Create github account
Git clone https://github.com/BhargavKChili/repo1.git    //click on code dropdown to get the url
ls
cd repo1 //you are inside repo
create file from here
Touch file1 //linux  command to create file
ls //to see the file is created
git status //to see where the file is  workspace or staging/index or local repo…it should be in workspace and in red colour
git add file1 //to move file from work space to staging
git status // file should be in green colour
git commit -m “Sample Commit” file1
git log //to see files in local repo commitid or shacode
git show cid
git push
cd .. //to come out of repo1/

